 Stylised symphony

 In 2000, some of the most outstanding musicians of the Leipziger Gewandhausorchester (Gewandhaus orchestra of Leipzig) got together and founded an ensemble called Leipziger Barocksolisten (Leipzig Baroque Soloists). They are John Roderick MacDonald (trumpet), Stefan Arzberger (violin), Thomas Hipper (oboe), Thomas Reinhardt (bassoon), Tobias Martin (double bass) and Michael Sch?nheit (harpsichord). Characterised by lively, spirited performances in diverse styles, their concert this evening features works by world-famous composers like Arcangelo Corelli, Johann Friedrich Fasch, Joseph Bodin de Boismortier, Gottfried Finger, Johann Pezel, Georg Friedrich H?ndel, Johann Sebastian Bach, Georg Philipp Teleman and Johann Wilhelm Hertel. It bears authentic testimony to the group?s dedication in fostering baroque tradition through the composers? rich variety of music, created between the beginning of the 17th and the first decades of the 18th century. Presented by Goethe-Institut and Calcutta School of Music.

 Event: A baroque music concert by Leipzig Baroque Soloists

 When: Today at 6.30 pm

 Where: St Paul?s Cathedral




